{
  "texts": [
    "People are sensible and sensitive human beings (Abram 2017).",
    "Therefore, they are prone to react to the pico-dynamics of bodily actions of their interlocutor (Blair and Cowley 2003; Thibault 2011).",
    "This dialogical aspect grounds languaging.",
    "A person's actions must be understood as responses to and interrelations with other people's actions (Linell 2009).",
    "Responding to these real-time events of utterance activity is essential to human becoming and grounds human presencing."
  ]
}